item.title: Jad uncompiler
item.dc:creator: @sonjichan sonjichan
item.description:
@sonjichan wrote:

jad, I believe you just place that in the folder with class files, and edit the batch file to include the files you want decompiled. There are much user friendly interface programs out there. Including DJ Java Decompiler and others. Jad is a batch however that I believe it’s not for newbies, but try editting the batch file to execute the file’s you want decompiled.
